article.headline: Bradley 75, N. Iowa 73
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Jeremy Crouch scored 20 of Bradley's last 26 points and the Braves held off Northern Iowa 75-73 on Saturday night. Crouch scored 23 of his season-high 28 points in the second half to help Bradley (8-9, 1-4 Missouri Valley) snap a six-game losing streak. Crouch was 6-of-8 from 3-point range to become the third player in school history to make 200 career 3s. Andrew Warren added 14 points for Bradley. Eric Coleman and Jared Josten each had 21 points for Northern Iowa (10-6, 2-3). The Panthers have lost three straight.
